<br>
That is why I think this whole marriage argument is BS. Now as I have said, if you want to grant them the rights of marriage, but call it something else, fine by me, and this seems to be what is suggested here. But can we agree that marriage by any other name is still marriage? I mean, how does changing the name to &quot;civil union&quot; suddenly make the &quot;institution of marriage&quot; safe? All it is doing is placating (or attempting to anyway) those who feel marriage is solely for straight couples.<br>
<br>
To me, this sounds like saying that smoking cigarettes is bad for you, but if we call them smoke sticks we somehow negate the damage. Hey, if that's what it takes to make gay marriages legal, it is a minuscule price to pay imo, but wouldn't you agree that is pretty silly and shows how weak the whole argument against gay marriage is? I mean... it can't be all that bad for us if simply changing the name negates any ill effects.<br>
