Sure, I'd be happy to.  I'm perfectly willing to provide support for any claims I make.  You may have noticed I've done it twice so far during this discussion.  Once in reference to who bears the burden of proof, and once in reference to adoption laws:<br>
<br>
Interracial marriage was illegal in some states as late as 1967, when the miscegenation laws were ruled unconstitutional by the Supreme Court; <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.oyez.org/oyez/resource/case/214/">Loving v. Virginia</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->  There's one source.  Feel free to do a search on Google for Supreme Court &quot;Loving v. Virginia&quot; for more.<br>
